syntax:

find [directorys] -name [filename]


---------------------------------------------------------
find is use to search file in directorys

* will use to match file pattern

----------------------------------------------------------
find /home/nidhsnt/ one.txt :will list the full path
find /home/nidhsnt/ one.*   :if u dont know the extention .use *
find /home/nidhsnt/ *.txt :will show only txt file
sudo find /home/nidhsnt/ *.txt :will show only txt file with sudo permisions